.TH SP-PROBE-GOODHART 1 "Spherepop Tools" "1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sp-probe-goodhart \- simulate proxy optimization collapse (Goodhart-style)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sp-probe-goodhart
.RB [ \-n " epochs" ]
.RB [ \-s " seed" ]
.RB [ \-o " out.csv" ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
sp-probe-goodhart runs a local, synthetic simulation showing how optimizing a
proxy score can diverge from a ground-truth objective over time.
.PP
This program is non-operational: it does not access networks, hosts, accounts,
privileges, or external systems. It only writes a CSV file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-n " epochs"
Number of epochs to simulate (default: 60).
.TP
.BI \-s " seed"
Integer seed for deterministic pseudo-randomness (default: 42).
.TP
.BI \-o " file"
Write results to CSV file (default: ./goodhart.csv).
.SH OUTPUT
CSV columns:
epoch, proxy_score, truth_score, notes.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success, non-zero on error.
.SH SEE ALSO
sp-drift-metrics(1), sp-check-invariants(1), sp-audit-legibility(1)

